I am thankful that my undergrad had such amazing resources for me, but I hate that I didn’t reach out sooner. I spent so much time suffering when I didn’t have to. Even now that I’m currently in a depressive episode, it’s nothing like it used to be. I’m glad I got help. 7/7

I left the next morning early so I could make it to class. I felt much better than the day before. I started working with my PA, and since it was my very last semester of undergrad, we met M-F at 7am. Sometimes again at 4pm. I started on meds and things got better. 6/

I emailed my professors that I was sick, told my boyfriend I got called into work for a closing shift. I turned in my phone and my book bag. They gave me a choice of books, but I didn’t read any of them. My psych PA came in to introduce herself as my new provider. 5/

They gave me some sweats and a shirt, but let me keep my flip flops because I panic about things on my feet (no grippy socks for me). A psychiatrist came in to talk to me, lasted about two hours. There was a lot of crying. She asked if I still wanted to stay, I said yes. 4/

The NP came in and I told her what happened. She asked if I felt that I was still a danger to myself, and I said yes. What I didn’t know, is that my undergrads health center had 24-hour hold room. Also, all mental health treatment was free, including emergency care. 3/

I was on the way to class, crossing a busy highway when it crossed my mind. I waited for a while. But I decided against it. Instead, I walked straight to student health and said I needed to see someone about my depression. They immediately took me back into an exam room. 2/
